 Oil and Natural Gas Commission Act, 1959: Section 13(1) & 32 Oil and Natural Gas Commission (Terms and Conditions of Appointment and Service) Regulations, 1975.' Regulation 3(2).
 Service Law--Pension--Temporary Government employees- Absorption in a statutory body. Oil and Natural Gas Commis- sion--No right to receive pension as a part of conditions of service before absorption--After absorption opting Contribu- tory Provident Fund and availing the benefit. Held not entitled to pension in addition to Provident Fund--Protec- tion of Section 13(1) and Regulation 3(2) held inapplicable--Section 12 of the Employees' Provident Funds and Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1952 not attracted.
